   <text>
      <front>
         <p>1898 June 4: to Mrs de Lisle<note xml:id="ftn3-903" place="foot" n="903"> MTG HB m64/14, m67/37, 57844.</note>
         </p>
      </front>
      <body>
         <p rend="end">Napier’<lb/>June 4<hi rend="sup ">th</hi>., 1898.</p>
         <p>Dear Mrs. de Lisle</p>
         <p>I have to thank you for your kind note—so full of good news <hi rend="italic">re </hi>your son:—I received it while inland, where I stayed much longer than I had intended, owing to kind-hearted folks &amp; fine weather: I returned last week &amp; have been <hi rend="italic">once </hi>in town since, but, having several little matters of business to attend, could not well call, [only look up in passing] but <hi rend="italic">fully intend </hi>to do so when I next go down, say some day of next week—if <hi rend="italic">fine</hi>. I trust <hi rend="italic">you </hi>(<hi rend="underline italic">all</hi>) are quite well &amp; happy.–</p>
         <p>I am Yours, faithy.,</p>
         <p>W. Colenso.</p>
      </body>
   </text>
